cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about developing a new method for automatically exploring architectures for visual recognition problems using Differentiable Architecture Search (DAS). The paper focuses on image and video recognition, which are subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves using gradient descent to efficiently search for architectures, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces several unique operations to encode spatio-temporal dynamics for video recognition, which falls under the subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves designing a schedule for gradually fixing the operations on the edges in the graph, which is a form of optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves exploring a large search space of architectures, which is a common task in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
